text:
Oneida is a city in Nemaha County, Kansas, United States. As of the 2010 census, 75 people lived there.
History.
Oneida was planned out about 1873. It was named after the Oneida people. The town's streets were named after the main thoroughfares of Chicago.
Geography.
According to the United States Census Bureau says that the city has a total area of. All of it is land.
2010 census.
As of the 2010 census says that there were 75 people, 26 households, and 17 families living in the city.
